                            <comment id="10699" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2004 19:56:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report - there is indeed an issue! Bean definitions without classes are not excluded from autowiring type checks, so cause the error you experienced there. Note that such bean definitions should properly work when not using autowiring!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding the error message: That IllegalStateException is normally wrapped with a BeanCreationException that gives contextual information like the bean name etc. It was just thrown in an unexpected place here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
